main event: A civilian reported observing a single unidentified object for 20 minutes in Indianapolis, Indiana on August 3, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed from the ground at around 10-12 miles east of Indianapolis, Indiana.
The object was in sight continuously for 20 minutes.
The sky was described as bright and cloudy.
The observer reported the object made no sound.
The observer was unable to estimate the speed or distance of the object.
